   HTML-hypertext markup language
      it has collections of pre-defined tag. that use to create basic structure of web page
      the html tags use to collect input from use to display output to user via web page
      the Html tags has limited property and value. 
      due to this limitation CSS required

     How HTML & CSS work ?
     Responsive webpage = HTML (tags) + CSS (property & values)
     Tag?
      <> - open tag
      </> - close tag
     Type of tags in html ?
     1. input tags - It use to collect many type of input from user
     2. Output tags - It use to display different type of output to use via browser

     Structure of html tags ?
     1. Dependent tag - those tags that open seperate and close seperate.
      Example:-
              <html> </html>
              <body> </body>
     2. Independent tag - those tags that has only open.
      Example:-
              <img>
              <br>
              <hr>
     React + Angular will not support independent tag.

     3. self closing tag - those html tags, that open and close together.
        Example:-
             <img/>
             <br/>
             <hr/>
     Behaviour of html tags ?
     1. block level tag -> those html tags , that print statement in newline.
     
     2. inline tag -> those html tag,that print statement in same line (side by side)
     -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
     => Tags
       <> open , </> close

     => Type of tags 
      1. input tag - it collect input from user
      2. output tag - it display output to user 

      => Structure of tags 
      1. dependent -<h1></h1> - open close seperate
      2. independent - <br> - only open
      3. self closing - </br> - open,close

      => Behaviour of tag
      1. block level tag - it print in new line
      2. inline tag - it print in same line
